ce:section.ce:para:
Simulated and actual XRD patterns of the pure MIL-101-SO3H microcrystals and amino-CQDs@MIL-101-SO3H composite, respectively are shown in Fig. 2
                        a. The XRD pattern of the prepared amino-CQDs@MIL-101-SO3H composite was consistent with that simulated from the MIL-101 single-crystal XRD data [33,35] indicating that the sulfo-modified MIL-101 framework was maintained even after immobilization of the amino-CQDs. The FT-IR spectra of amino-CQDs@MIL-101-SO3H and MIL-101-SO3H were almost identical (Fig. 2b), indicating that the chemical structure of MIL-101-SO3H was retained even after immobilization of the amino-CQDs in the MIL-101-SO3H skeleton. Field-emission SEM images revealed that amino-CQDs@MIL-101-SO3H and MIL-101-SO3H had the same size and same octahedral morphology (Fig. 3
                        ). Energy-dispersive X-ray mapping analyses supported the encapsulation of the amino-CQDs in the MIL-101-SO3H framework (Fig. 4
                        ). Elemental distributions of N, C, S, O, and Cr in the amino-CQDs@MIL-101-SO3H composite were completely overlapped, indicating the uniform dispersion of the amino-CQDs in the MIL-101-SO3H framework.
